{"blocks":[{"key":"ehip4","text":"Or transfer 1-2 drops of the conidial suspension","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"72t2u","text":"In some cases you will need more drops, for Aspergillus flavus for example","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"italic","offset":44,"length":18}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"899u1","text":"Visually compare the suspension to the 0.5 McFarland Standard and make adjustments as described until the suspension visually matches the standard","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"b3lr1","text":"  ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"offset":0,"length":1}],"data":{}},{"key":"frmjb","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{"0":{"type":"image","mutability":"MUTABLE","data":{"guid":"8FA6AAD07D0011ED9FA97730D7D8DD43","height":733,"id":324155,"is_video":false,"legend":"","mime":"image/png","nestedSelector":null,"original_name":"Inoculum suspension.png","placeholder":"https://s3.amazonaws.com/protocols-files/files/j6t7bwrzf.jpg","shadow":true,"source":"https://s3.amazonaws.com/protocols-files/files/j6t5bwrzf.jpg","webp_placeholder":"https://s3.amazonaws.com/protocols-files/files/j6t6bwrzf.webp","webp_source":"https://s3.amazonaws.com/protocols-files/files/j6t4bwrzf.webp","width":550}}}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"9907k","text":"Adjustment is made by adding more destilled water if the suspension is very turbid and more conidia if the turbidity is very low.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"argmi","text":"Dip a sterile cotton swab in the inoculum suspension and rub the entire surface of the control plate in a back-and-forth motion ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"5eptg","text":"Re-dip the cotton swab and rub the entire surface in the same way of each of the three remaining plates with the azoles","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"4i2gn","text":"Incubate the plates at 35-37°C for   and observe growth.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"offset":35,"length":1}],"data":{}},{"key":"9krmh","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{"0":{"type":"duration","mutability":"MUTABLE","data":{"duration":172800,"guid":"8FB3B9407CF711ED9FA97730D7D8DD43","id":0,"label":"","pause":null,"preset":[],"start":null}}}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"pepa","text":"Visual analysis score definition: ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"2aiv4","text":"0: no visible growth","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"cic0p","text":"1: weak/minimal growth (such as \u003e5 tiny colonies or confluent weak growth where isolate was inoculated (covering ≤ half of the plate)","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"521nc","text":"2: clearly visible growth with hyphal extension, but not covering entire plate ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"fuq51","text":"3: prominent uninhibited growth covering most of the plate","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
